{"key":"processedPost-11930805","value":{"id":11930805,"first":11923406,"last":12058356,"when":1264894337,"utime":"01/31/10 01:32 AM","content":"The yellow color of the straw indicates it's wheat straw.&nbsp; The pods you find in straw are left over grains the combine missed, or are from weeds that were in the field when the straw was baled up and shouldn't cause too much problem.&nbsp; Pick out what of them you can, but don't get anal trying to get every one.&nbsp; The benefit of straw is very fast colonization, so hopefully if you compress it properly, those weed pods will colonize before they contaminate.&nbsp; <br /><br />Soak in soapy water for 2 hours, or in regular water for 12 to 24 hours, and then pasteurize at 140F to 160F for 90 minutes to 2 hours.&nbsp; Drain, cool, and inoculate.<br />RR","title":"Re: Is this the right STRAW","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}